sec.p:
Pre-specified subgroup analyses were performed according to participants‚Äô baseline hypertension status, diabetes status, and plasma lipids for the outcomes of BP, glycaemia, and lipid profile, respectively. Hypertension status was defined by:
GP record coding as hypertensive;
taking antihypertensive medication;
baseline SBP >140 mmHg; or
baseline DBP >90 mmHg.

Owing to inconsistent coding for hyperlipidaemia between datasets, clinical thresholds for baseline values were used to define abnormal plasma lipids:
total cholesterol >5 mmol/L;
HDL <1 mmol/L;
calculated LDL >3 mmol/L; or
TG (Triglycerides) >1.7 mmol/L.
